    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` said unto Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]`, etc.] Being come into his bedchamber, and sitting by him, or standing before him: God Almighty appeared unto at Luz in the land of Canaan `[nation_Canaan_Gen_15]`; the same with Bethel, where God appeared, both at his going to Padanaram, and at his [v_Gen_28_11] [v_Gen_28_12] [v_Gen_28_13] [v_Gen_28_14] [v_Gen_28_15] [v_Gen_28_16] [v_Gen_28_17] [v_Gen_28_18] [v_Gen_28_19] return from thence, (<012811>Genesis 28:11-19 35:6-12); which of those times is here referred to is not certain; very likely he refers to them both, since the same promises were made to him at both times, as after mentioned: and blessed me; promised he would bless him, both with temporal and spiritual blessings, as he did as follows.\nVer."
