    "Commentary Vol. 83": "And thy issue, which thou begettest after them, shall be thine, etc.] The children of Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]`, that either were, or would be begotten after Ephraim `[char_Ephraim_Gen_41]` and Manasseh; though whether ever any were is not certain; and this is only mentioned by way of supposition, as Jarchi interprets it, \u201cif thou shouldest beget\u201d, etc. these should be reckoned his own, and not as Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]`\u2019s sons, but be considered as other grandchildren of Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]`\u2019s were, and not as Ephraim `[char_Ephraim_Gen_41]` and Manasseh: [and] shall be called after the name of their brethren in their inheritance; they should not have distinct names, or make distinct tribes, or have a distinct inheritance; but should be called either the children of Ephraim `[char_Ephraim_Gen_41]`, or the children of Manasseh, and should be reckoned as belonging either to the one tribe, or the other, and have their inheritance in them, and with them, and not separate.\nVer."
